public class FullFactorialExperiment
extends AbstractMultiExperiment

Systematically tests all possible combinations of various factors and their values on a base experiment.

addFactor

public void addFactor(String name,
                      Object value)
Adds a configuration to test.

Parameters:
name - The factor name. This should be the name of a Java Beans Property of the base experiment, otherwise execution of the experiment will fail. In case value is a FullFactorialExperiment.ComplexFactorSetter, name can be arbitrary.
value - The value to test for factor name.

addFactors

public <E extends Enum<?>> void addFactors(String factorName,
                                           Class<E> enumClass)
Convenience method to set a factor "factorName" for all possible values of an enumeration.

Say an experiment has a property "color" of type ColorEnum 

 enum ColorEnum {
        RED, GREEN, BLUE
 }
than calling addFactors("color",ColorEnum.class) would be equivalent to manually adding three configurations: 
 addFactor("color", RED);
 addFactor("color", GREEN);
 addFactor("color", BLUE);

See Also:
addFactor(String, Object)

addFactors

public void addFactors(String factorName,
                       Object[] values)
Convenience method to add all elements in values as a possible value for a factor/property factorName. This method is equivalent to repeatedly calling addFactor(String, Object) for each element in values.

See Also:
